    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>Alice had a bag where each number from <b>1</b> to <b>N</b> was present in it. After a magic trick she either removes all even numbers or all odd numbers from the bag.</p>\n<p>Given the kind of trick she has performed find the <b>P<sup>th</sup></b> smallest number in the bag after the trick. For example <b>P = 1</b> denotes the smallest number present.</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>First line contains <b>T</b>, the number of test cases. Each test case consists of <b>N</b>, a string <b>S</b> and an integer <b>P</b> in single line.</p>\n<p><b>S</b> will be either <b>\u201codd\u201d</b> or <b>\u201ceven\u201d</b>(quotes for clarity), denoting the kind of trick Alice has performed.</p>\n<p>Note: It is guaranteed that <b>P</b> will be less than or equal to remaining items in the bag.</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case, print the required answer in one line.\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<p>Should contain all the constraints on the input data that you may have. Format it like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1 \u2264 T \u2264 100</b></li>\n<li><b>1 \u2264 N \u2264 10<sup>3</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>P \u2265 1</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n4 odd 2\n5 even 2\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n4\n3\n</pre><p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example 1.</b><br />\nAfter performing the <b>\u201codd\u201d</b> trick the numbers 1 and 3 get removed from the bag.<br />\nNumbers 2 and 4 are left in the bag.<br />\n2nd smallest number is 4 now.<br /></p>\n<p><b>Example 2.</b><br />\nAfter performing the <b>\u201ceven\u201d</b> trick the numbers 2 and 4 get removed from the bag.<br />\nNumbers 1, 3 and 5 are left in the bag.<br />\n2nd smallest number is 3 now.\n</p>\n",
